                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="46118" author="ian" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 01:23:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Both patches 4159 and 4148 landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45907" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 17:57:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sure, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45906" author="prakash" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 17:55:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alex, James, please see: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4159&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4159&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45904" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 17:25:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just uploaded that. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45901" author="morrone" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 17:05:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patchset 2 + ldiskfs enabled would be great, yes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45900" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 16:58:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris, if you&apos;d prefer to land the minimal patch now, I&apos;m fine with patchset #2 (+ ldiskfs enabled by default).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45895" author="morrone" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 16:17:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You need to get me an explanation of why we can&apos;t do this now, and exactly when it will be landed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45894" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 16:10:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris, this is not just obdfilter - it&apos;s llog-lvfs code which I&apos;d like to avoid from the builds with no ldiskfs support.&lt;br/&gt;
In orion it&apos;s easier because llog-lvfs itself was removed, we can&apos;t do this now on master. and this is one of examples&lt;br/&gt;
why we can&apos;t just land orion on master (as we&apos;d like to do as well).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45892" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 15:23:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The last patch for this ticket was trying to build obdfilter for zfs which is not needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45882" author="morrone" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 13:55:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you explain why ZFS needs that?  As of 2.3.51 we are building lustre --without-ldiskfs and --with-zfs and did not see a build problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In any event, the obdfilter code will be deleted in about a week, as I understand it, so I don&apos;t much care either way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45874" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 12:51:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Almost. Only the ZFS build now fails. What is missing is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;diff --git a/lustre/obdfilter/autoMakefile.am b/lustre/obdfilter/autoMakefile.am&lt;br/&gt;
index 171bc30..3896641 100644&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8212; a/lustre/obdfilter/autoMakefile.am&lt;br/&gt;
+++ b/lustre/obdfilter/autoMakefile.am&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -35,7 +35,9 @@&lt;br/&gt;
 #&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; if MODULES&lt;br/&gt;
+if LDISKFS_ENABLED&lt;br/&gt;
 modulefs_DATA = obdfilter$(KMODEXT)&lt;br/&gt;
 endif&lt;br/&gt;
+endif&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; MOSTLYCLEANFILES := @MOSTLYCLEANFILES@ &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45868" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 11:30:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just submitted. All yours now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45866" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 11:08:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll have to update the patch after that. thanks in advance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45864" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 11:06:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Found the last build bug on client. Will be pushing a patch soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45860" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 10:22:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixing..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45857" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 09:20:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Client build seems to be having a issue as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45856" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 09:16:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James, there is a small defect still in the code (preventing few conf-sanity tests), I&apos;ll upload fixed version shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45854" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 09:00:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trying it as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45853" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 08:53:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i&apos;m uploading a new version just to see how the build system like it..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45852" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 08:52:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;no, neither mds nor cmm are used with any backend.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45851" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 08:49:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Last patch is pretty broken. Is mds and cmm used only for ldisk non-osd mode? I included them back in for server build or should they be only ldiskfs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45844" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 08:10:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;not at all. thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45842" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 08:04:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would you mind if I add in the top autoMakefile.am fix for the META for ldisk?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45841" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 08:02:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks for the patch. I&apos;ve slightly modified it so that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) utilities (mkfs/mount) do not try to call ldiskfs helpers&lt;br/&gt;
2) enable ldiskfs by default (sorry, there are number of people and systems depending on this behavior)&lt;br/&gt;
3) the code depending on lvfs/ldiskfs shouldn&apos;t build unless ldiskfs support is configured: obdfilter, llog_lvfs, backup in mgc&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45826" author="prakash" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 20:42:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed an initial patch to remedy this here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4148&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4148&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45819" author="prakash" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 17:04:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To start, it looks like my patches from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2158&quot; title=&quot;remove lvfs and fsfilt code&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2158&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ORI-257&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; were dropped. I&apos;m going to try and resurrect those on master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
